{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "controversial-professional",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "![CC](https://i.creativecommons.org/l/by/4.0/88x31.png)\n",
    "\n",
    "This work is licensed under a [Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License](http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/).\n",
    "\n",
    "# Analyzing PIV data of a longitudinal vortex\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we analyze particle image velocimetry (PIV) data of a dynamically meandering longitudinal vortex. The data were recorded and provided by [Nils Rathje](https://www.tu-braunschweig.de/en/ism/research/aerodynamics-of-aircraft/staff/rathje) of TU Braunschweig's institut of fluid mechanics as part of a DFG-funded project. A delta-wing configuration with a swept angle of $65^\\circ$ was investigated in the institut's low-speed wind tunnel ([MUB](https://www.tu-braunschweig.de/ism/institutsausstattung/windkanalanlagen/mub)) by means of a time-resolved stero-PIV. The data were recorded with a frequency of $3kHz$ with $7ms$ between double frames using the software package DaVis 8.4 by [Lavision](https://www.lavision.de/en/products/flowmaster/2d-stereo-piv/index.php). A final window size decreased to $32\\times 32 px^2$ was used with $50\\%$ overlap, which corresponds to a resolution of $\\Delta x = \\Delta y = 1,5mm \\left( \\widehat{=} 16px \\right)$.\n",
    "\n",
    "The flow conditions may be summarized as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "- free stream velocity $U_{\\infty}=55.5 m/s$\n",
    "- Reynolds number $Re\\approx 0.99\\times 10^6$\n",
    "- ambient temperature $T\\approx 37^\\circ C$\n",
    "- angle of attack $\\alpha = 8^\\circ$\n",
    "\n",
    "<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n",
    "The analysis is still preliminary and will be updated in future versions of flowTorch.\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "potential-helen",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import bisect\n",
    "import torch as pt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "from flowtorch.data import CSVDataloader, mask_sphere\n",
    "from flowtorch import DATASETS\n",
    "from flowtorch.analysis import SVD\n",
    "\n",
    "# increase resolution of plots\n",
    "mpl.rcParams['figure.dpi'] = 160"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "characteristic-america",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Checking and accessing the available data\n",
    "\n",
    "The data were exported from DaVis as *.csv* files, with one file for each snapshot. All snapshots are stored in the same folder. The `CSVDataloader` class has a class method `from_davis` to access such a data structure. The file name syntax in the sample data follows the pattern *BXXXXX.dat*, where *XXXXX* correspondes the the snapshot's index. Therefore, we pass *B* as prefix argument to distinguish the index from the rest of the file name. The default suffix is *.dat*, but it can be overwritten by passing a suffix argument."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "advised-personal",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "First and last snapshot: 00001/05000\n",
      "Available fields:  ['Vx', 'Vy', 'Vz']\n",
      "Available measurement points: 3741\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "path = DATASETS[\"csv_aoa8_beta0_xc100_stereopiv\"]\n",
    "loader = CSVDataloader.from_davis(path, prefix=\"B\")\n",
    "times = loader.write_times\n",
    "fields = loader.field_names[times[0]]\n",
    "vertices = loader.vertices\n",
    "print(f\"First and last snapshot: {times[0]}/{times[-1]}\")\n",
    "print(\"Available fields: \", fields)\n",
    "print(f\"Available measurement points: {vertices.shape[0]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "accepting-saudi",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Vx, Vy, Vz = loader.load_snapshot(fields, times)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "young-nomination",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Flow field analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "First we compute and visualize the spatial mean of each velocity component over time (the mean velocity over all measurement points in a single snapshot). The spatial average, denoted by $\\langle\\rangle_s$, is an easy means to identify potential nonstationary trends or outliers in the data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "diverse-miniature",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1280x640 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axarr = plt.subplots(3, 1, figsize=(8, 4), sharex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "n_times = Vx.shape[1]\n",
    "freq = 3000.0\n",
    "times_num = pt.linspace(0.0, n_times/freq, n_times)\n",
    "\n",
    "labels = [r\"$\\langle V_{:s} \\rangle_s$\".format(coord) for coord in [\"x\", \"y\", \"z\"]]\n",
    "for i, (vel, label) in enumerate(zip([Vx, Vy, Vz], labels)):\n",
    "    axarr[i].plot(times_num, vel.mean(dim=0), lw=1, label=label)\n",
    "    axarr[i].set_ylabel(r\"{:s} in $m/s$\".format(label))\n",
    "    axarr[i].yaxis.set_major_formatter(mpl.ticker.FormatStrFormatter(\"%2.2f\"))\n",
    "axarr[-1].set_xlim(0, times_num[-1])\n",
    "axarr[-1].set_xlabel(r\"$t$ in $s$\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "technical-success",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the next step, we visualize the temporal mean and the corresponding standard deviation in each measurement point. In the resulting fields, we may be able to identify potenial outliers or areas of extreme values, e.g., close to the boundaries of the recorded images."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "interior-entertainment",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1280x400 with 6 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axarr = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(8, 2.5), sharex=True, sharey=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "axarr[0, 0].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vx.mean(dim=1), levels=15, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "axarr[0, 1].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vy.mean(dim=1), levels=15, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "axarr[0, 2].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vz.mean(dim=1), levels=15, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "axarr[1, 0].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vx.std(dim=1), levels=15, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "axarr[1, 1].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vy.std(dim=1), levels=15, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "axarr[1, 2].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vz.std(dim=1), levels=15, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# title for each column\n",
    "for ax, title in zip(axarr[0, :], [r\"$V_x$\", r\"$V_y$\", r\"$V_z$\"]):\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "# label for each row\n",
    "axarr[0, 0].set_ylabel(\"mean\")\n",
    "axarr[1, 0].set_ylabel(\"std.\")\n",
    "# preserve aspect ratio\n",
    "for row in range(2):\n",
    "    for col in range(3):\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].set_aspect(\"equal\", \"box\")\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].xaxis.set_major_locator(plt.MaxNLocator(6))\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].yaxis.set_major_locator(plt.MaxNLocator(5))\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].grid(True, c=\"w\", ls=\"--\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "overall-catalog",

    "We also visualize a couple of randomly selected snapshots to have a second simple sanity check."
   ]

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "posted-publicity",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1280x1120 with 15 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "n_select = 5\n",
    "snapshots = np.random.choice(range(n_times), n_select)\n",
    "\n",
    "height=1.4\n",
    "fig, axarr = plt.subplots(n_select, 3, figsize=(8, height*n_select), sharex=True, sharey=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "def color_bounds(field, factor=5):\n",
    "    mean = pt.mean(field)\n",
    "    std = pt.std(field)\n",
    "    return {\"vmin\" : mean-factor*std,\n",
    "            \"vmax\" : mean+factor*std}\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, snap in enumerate(snapshots):\n",
    "    axarr[i, 0].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vx[:, snap], levels=15, cmap=\"jet\", **color_bounds(Vx))\n",
    "    axarr[i, 1].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vy[:, snap], levels=15, cmap=\"jet\", **color_bounds(Vy))\n",
    "    axarr[i, 2].tricontourf(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], Vz[:, snap], levels=15, cmap=\"jet\", **color_bounds(Vz))\n",
    "    axarr[i, 0].set_ylabel(f\"snapshot {snap}\")\n",
    "    for ax in axarr[i, :]:\n",
    "        ax.set_aspect(\"equal\", \"box\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "for ax, title in zip(axarr[0, :], [r\"$V_x$\", r\"$V_y$\", r\"$V_z$\"]):\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

    "## SVD analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "lesser-commonwealth",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Masking the data\n",
    "\n",
    "In the visualizations above, we could observe:\n",
    "- spurious values (close to zero) close to the borders, which are particularly pronounced in the $z$-component of the velocity\n",
    "- a zone of spurious values in the upper right corner of the image\n",
    "\n",
    "These spurious samples might compromise our analysis, which is why we create a mask to exclude the affected regions from the data. For the longitudinal vortex, a circular/spherical mask is suitable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "identified-consciousness",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Selected vertices: 1018/3741\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mask = mask_sphere(vertices, center=[-10.0, 15], radius=35)\n",
    "print(f\"Selected vertices: {mask.sum().item()}/{mask.shape[0]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "requested-ballot",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "ax.scatter(vertices[:, 0], vertices[:, 1], s=0.5, c=mask)\n",
    "ax.set_aspect(\"equal\", 'box')\n",
    "ax.set_xlim(vertices[:, 0].min(), vertices[:, 0].max())\n",
    "ax.set_ylim(vertices[:, 1].min(), vertices[:, 1].max())\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(r\"$x$ in $mm$\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(r\"$y$ in $mm$\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "diagnostic-acquisition",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Visualizing the SVD\n",
    "\n",
    "In the present analysis, we are only analyzing the velocity in the main flow direction, which is the $z$-component."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "endless-pension",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# allocate reduced data matrix matrix, apply the mask to the original data, and subtract the mean\n",
    "selected_points = mask.sum().item()\n",
    "Vz_masked = pt.zeros((selected_points, Vz.shape[1]), dtype=pt.float32)\n",
    "for i in range(Vz.shape[1]):\n",
    "    Vz_masked[:, i] = pt.masked_select(Vz[:, i], mask)\n",
    "Vz_mean = Vz_masked.mean(dim=1).unsqueeze(-1)\n",
    "Vz_masked -= Vz_mean"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "boxed-interface",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we compute the singular value decomposition and visualize the singular values, the POD modes (left singular vectors) and the mode coefficients (right singular vectors multiplied by the corresponding singular value). The modes can be interpreted as coherent spatial structures while the coefficients characterize the modes' evolution over time."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "moral-period",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "SVD of a 1018x5000 data matrix\n",
      "Selected/optimal rank: 5000/349\n",
      "data type: torch.float32 (4b)\n",
      "truncated SVD size: 23.3740Mb\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# we set the rank to to the number of available snapshots to avoid any truncation\n",
    "svd = SVD(Vz_masked, 5000)\n",
    "print(svd)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "swedish-setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "s = svd.s\n",
    "s_sum = s.sum().item()\n",
    "# relative contribution\n",
    "s_rel = [s_i / s_sum * 100 for s_i in s]\n",
    "# cumulative contribution\n",
    "s_cum = [s[:n].sum().item() / s_sum * 100 for n in range(s.shape[0])]\n",
    "# find out how many singular values we need to reach at least 99 percent\n",
    "i_99 = bisect.bisect_right(s_cum, 99)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "tropical-directory",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "first 932 singular values yield 99.01%\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 960x640 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, 1, sharex=True)\n",
    "ax1.bar(range(s.shape[0]), s_rel, align=\"edge\")\n",
    "ax2.plot(range(s.shape[0]), s_cum)\n",
    "ax2.set_xlim(0, 200)\n",
    "ax2.set_ylim(0, 105)\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"individual contribution in %\")\n",
    "ax2.set_title(\"cumulative contribution in %\")\n",
    "ax2.plot([0, i_99, i_99], [s_cum[i_99], s_cum[i_99], 0], ls=\"--\", color=\"C3\")\n",
    "print(\"first {:d} singular values yield {:1.2f}%\".format(i_99, s_cum[i_99]))\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "imperial-spread",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [

     "data": {

    "fig, axarr = plt.subplots(3, 3, figsize=(8, 6), sharex=True, sharey=True)\n",
    "x = pt.masked_select(vertices[:, 0], mask)\n",
    "y = pt.masked_select(vertices[:, 1], mask)\n",
    "count = 0\n",
    "for row in range(3):\n",
    "    for col in range(3):\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].tricontourf(x, y, svd.U[:, count], levels=14, cmap=\"jet\")\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].set_aspect(\"equal\", 'box')\n",
    "        # add 1 for the POD mode number since we subtracted the mean\n",
    "        axarr[row, col].set_title(f\"mode {count + 1}\")\n",
    "        count += 1\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
